annotationA: Catalyzes the hydrolysis of phosphatidylinositol-4,5- bisphosphate (PtdIns-4,5-P2) to phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate (PtdIns-4-P)
annotationB: 1-phosphatidylinositol-4-phosphate 5-kinase activity; 1-phosphatidylinositol-5-phosphate 4-kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: actin filament organization; phosphatidylinositol phosphorylation; regulation of cell shape; regulation of TOR signaling; positive regulation of multicellular organism growth; cell adhesion; positive regulation of cell growth; phosphorylation
